=========yorg=========
===subject:response to Stephanie
===from:Laura Johnson
===date:Wed Jun 25  8:39:55 2003
===message:Specifically, our recent “regime change” in Iraq was unnecessary, because it was based on outright lies about the existence of weapons of mass destruction and the American public's misconceived notion that Saddam Hussein had anything to do with the attacks on the World Trade Center. In addition, there was no reason for the United States to be involved in the conflict in Vietnam. Interestingly enough, our involvement there was also based on an outright lie – regarding “unprovoked attacks” on US destroyers that should never have been in the Gulf of Tonkin in the first place.
<p>
Based on the wars and regional and ethnic conflicts that have taken place in the past century, I conclude there is much passion and rationalization – but very little reason – behind any war.

=========yorg=========
